This paper deals with the design of beamforming vectors for multiple-input multiple-output (MIMO) radar systems, which involves signal processing and optimization techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also discusses the practical application of the beamforming vectors in MIMO radar systems, which could fall under cs.SI (Signal Processing), cs.SY (Systems and Control), or cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Additionally, the paper presents a method for selecting the best beamforming vectors, which could be related to machine learning and optimization, and thus could also fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning).
